We prove minimax theorems for lower semicontinuous functions defined on a Hilbert space.
 The main tool is the theory of $\Phi$-convex functions and 

sufficient and necessary conditions for the minimax equality to hold for  $\Phi$-convex  functions.

These conditions are expressed in terms of abstract  $\Phi$-subgradients.

